Task 3
Automate the shutdown of Ubuntu Instances only using Ansible Conditionals

Hint: Use when condition on ansible gather_facts


Here first you need to create inventory.ini 
[all]
ec2-user@Ip
ubuntu@Ip
ubuntu@Ip

You might think to group them and do this right ,
Yes you can but the issue can be you dont know what are the instances in the ini file are whether ubuntu/linux and ultimately the requirement is you need to use when condition on ansible gather_facts
see the ansible_facts takes from the gathering_facts -->Gathering facts collects many details about the targets in that you can see details ,
For example you can give as 

 tasks:
    - name: Print all the ansible gathered ansible_facts 
      ansible.builtin.debug:
        var: ansible_facts

---
- hosts: all
  become: true

  tasks:
    - name: Shutdown ubuntu instances only
      ansible.builtin.command: /sbin/shutdown -t now   --> we are shutting down now
      when:
       ansible_facts['os_family'] == "Debian"   


